%S A383758 1,2,6,24,93,1952,14412,361881
%N A383758 Least integer k for which sigma(k - x) + sigma(k + x) = n*k has at least one nonnegative solution.
%C A383758 The corresponding x are : 0,0,0,0,87,1828,13308,358839, ...
%F A383758 a(n) <= A317681(n).
%e A383758 a(5) = 24 because the equation sigma(24-x) + sigma(24+x) = 5*24 has the solution x = 0. This is verified as follows: sigma(24-0) + sigma(24+0) = sigma(24) + sigma(24) = 60 + 60 = 120 = 5*24. Moreover, no smaller number possesses this unique property.
%e A383758 a(6) = 93 because the equation sigma(93 - x) + sigma(93 + x) = 6 * 93 has the solution x = 87: sigma(93 - 87) + sigma(93 + 87) = sigma(6) + sigma(180) = 12 + 546 = 6*93. Moreover, no smaller number possesses this unique property.
%o A383758 (PARI) isok(k,n) = forstep(x=k-1, 0, -1, if (sigma(k - x) + sigma(k + x) == n*k, return(1)));
%o A383758 a(n) = my(k=1); while (!isok(k, n), k++); k; \\ _Michel Marcus_, May 10 2025
